              },
              "free_text": [
                " NBS linac neutron TOF facility."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The detector contained five fission foils with 100",
                "microg/cm2 deposits of 237Np evaporated onto both",
                "sides of 0.0025 cm aluminum backings."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N",
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Multiplate fission ionization chambers."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two (237Np and 235U) fission chambers were",
                "located at the 63.65-m flight path. An annular proton",
                "telescope and polyethylene films were used to measure",
                "the energy dependence of the neutron flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The shape of the neutron flux was obtained by",
                "dividing the count rate vs. TOF data from proton",
                "telescope by the hydrogen scattering cross section,",
                "taking into account the angular range of the proton",
                "recoils. The fission chamber data were then divided",
                "by the flux which had been interpolated to the same",
                "energy mesh."
              ]
            }
          ],
